HEADWORD: Clubbish
<hw>Club"bish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Rude;
clownish.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disposed to club together; <as>as, a
